    <summary>Synchronizes qBittorrent's listening port with the port assigned by your VPN provider</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
## qbPortWeaver

qbPortWeaver is a lightweight Windows system tray application that automatically keeps qBittorrent's listening port in sync with the port assigned by your VPN provider — no manual updates needed.

### Supported VPN Providers

- **ProtonVPN** — via log file parsing (default) or NAT-PMP
- **Private Internet Access (PIA)** — via `piactl` CLI
- **NAT-PMP (RFC 6886)** — works with any NAT-PMP capable VPN client or router

### Features

- **Automatic port sync** — detects VPN port changes and updates qBittorrent via its Web API
- **Tray status indicator** — color-coded dot (green / orange / red) shows sync status at a glance; tooltip displays current port without opening the log
- **Multi-VPN support** — ProtonVPN, PIA, and NAT-PMP selectable from Settings
- **Restart qBittorrent after port change** — ensures port changes take effect immediately
- **Force start qBittorrent** — launches qBittorrent automatically if it is not running
- **Default port fallback** — apply a fallback port when the VPN is disconnected
- **Restart on disconnect** — optionally restart qBittorrent when the connection drops
- **Interface mismatch warning** — alerts if qBittorrent is not bound to the VPN adapter
- **Post-update command** — run a custom script after each successful port update
- **Automatic update checker** — notifies when a new release is available on GitHub
- **Windows startup integration** — optional auto-start with Windows
- **File-based logging** — automatic log rotation; debug mode available
- **JSON status file** — written after each sync cycle for external monitoring

For setup instructions, configuration details, and recommended settings, see the full documentation at https://github.com/martsg666/qbPortWeaver#readme
    ]]></description>
